{"id": "1385110284116430931", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "702167871144591461", "author_name": "_venush", "content": "The feel of him trembling against you, claws digging into the folds of your clothes (because even now, as he unravels at your fingertips, he is so mindful of your safety). The way he would bury his face into the sheets if you let him, the tips of his ears flushed red peeking out between the white of his hair. The emerald of his eyes that shimmers, misty, and the way he always, always answers your call with such an earnest, heartfelt look -- trembling though it is at the moment. The way he bites his lips, near bloodied by his fangs, as your fingers brush through his feathers and linger at the base of his wings.", "timestamp": "2025-06-19T04:13:45.838000+00:00", "reactions": [{"emoji": "❤️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 3}]}
{"id": "1385110337430491146", "channel_id": "1326453763355185215", "author_id": "702167871144591461", "author_name": "_venush", "content": "The trust, woven unspoken. He asks, pressed into your sheets: teach me, show me.", "timestamp": "2025-06-19T04:13:58.549000+00:00"}
